::: {.content-box-solid-lightorange .fragment fragment-index=3 .fade-in-then-out}
**Repelling-Attracting Hamiltonian Monte Carlo** 

1. Given state $q$, sample _auxiliary momentum_ $p$[$\sim \mathcal{N}(0, \Sigma)$]{.footnotesize}+br+br
2. For $(q, p) \sim e^{-H(q,\, p)}$ in the joint state-space+br
treat [$H(q, p)$]{.footnotesize} as the **Hamiltonian of a physical system**+br+br
3. For time $T$ simulate **conformal Hamiltonian dynamics**:
  * _anti-dissipative_ dynamics for $0 < t < T/2$ 
  * _dissipative_ dynamics for $T/2 < t < T$
4. Accept/Reject the proposed state with probability+br
[$\hspace{4em}\displaystyle\alpha(q', q) = \min\pb{ 1, {e^{-H(q',\  p')}}\Big/ e^{-H(q',\  p')} }$]{.footnotesize .center}
:::

::: {.content-box-solid-lightorange .fragment .fade-in-then-out fragment-index=5}
+br+br+br+br
RA-HMC is tuning-free and can efficiently sample from multimodal distributions across 1000s of dimensions
[@vishwanath2024repelling]
+br+br+br+br
:::

